ield E is defined to be the force E felt by a unit point charge"},{"pid":"4851983e7eb4f208f10f80d273360fc0307dd8ce","tid":6878,"uid":1773,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-11-29T12:30:15.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>其實我係讀哲學，特別係metaphysics<br />\n<br />\n好多時佢哋講unit negative charge, unit mass之類，我完全唔知講緊咩<br />\n<br />\nUnit negative charge其實係咩嚟<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n所以我想進修下physics</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nunit charge 多數講緊electron charge<br />\nunit mass 就唔知喇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\nUnit quantity = 1 arbitrary unit of that quantity<br />\n<br />\ne.g. Electric field E is defined to be the force <span style=\"color: red;\">F</span> felt by a unit point charge</blockquote>"},{"pid":"79b97a4e9688b88480bb7a6ac6b0afcf6e601533","tid":6878,"uid":6801,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-11-29T12:31:57.000Z","msg":"Cosmology大佬都黎埋<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f4b0616a870d74216ae59afbe26e153ffd8e7bbc","tid":6878,"uid":41243,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-11-29T12:34:10.000Z","msg":"搵本數學書學下d single/multi-variable calculus, linear algebra, vector calculus<br />\n跟住就可以直接睇upper ug書架啦<br />\nem, qm: griffiths (qm griffiths好多人話唔好, 作為入門書其實我覺得ok, 唔通第一本就睇sakurai咩)<br />\nclassical mechanics: 呢個我都覺得操下基本野先比較好, 搵本halliday做下先, 跟住再搵本marion<br />\nthermo, stat mech: 我都唔知有乜書特別好"},{"pid":"2abd130e4ca86d7d8cb9eb35488b5e0af1dcb8a4","tid":6878,"uid":41243,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-11-29T12:34:39.000Z","msg":"不過輕輕鬆鬆就睇Feynman啦"}]}